//Image has solid Background (is not transparent) -> Start here!
Choose any image you want to make into an icon
Open in GIMP
Convert Background to Alpha
Crop Image to Content
Scale to at least 160x160px or any multitude of that
Export as .png

//Image has no Background (is transparent) -> Start here!
Open in Inkscape
Set Document Size to 160x160px or the multitude of resolution of the Image and set shown UoM to px
Create rectangle with Rectangle Tool
Set position to 0,0 and size to 160,160 or the multitude of resolution of the Image
Turn on Fill (color RGBA: fafafaff)
Turn on Stroke (White RGBA: fafafaff, Blue RGBA: 00a8e8ff, Black RGBA: 090909ff, Stroke Width 12px times the multitude of resolution of the Image)
Round Corners to Radius 16px on x and y Axis while still in Rectangle Tool
Moove Icon Layer to Foreground
Scale Icon to fit (This is why you create the Background, even if you will not use it)
Center Icon
If no Background is needed, moove Rectangle out of Document Area.
Export at 160x160px as Iconhyperlinkreference(eg.Website,YouTube,etc.)-160x160.png
Compress the Icon if necessary
Upload to https://github.com/Fatty-Do-Do/HSR-Konstanz-E-Mail-Signature-Assets/tree/65e965bcdfe8a7330497d5698f795cef61985c6f/General

